Built the Minesweeper game at `minesweeper/index.html`.

**Design adherence**
- Apple-inspired minimal: `#fafafa` bg, `#1d1d1f` text, `#6e6e73` secondary, `#0071e3` accent. No glow, no neon.
- Font stack matches spec (SF Pro Display / system).
- Top-left minimal `←` floating pill back button to `../index.html`.
- Pill-style difficulty tabs and tap-mode toggle, 44px reset button, card-based panel with soft shadow.
- All English copy: "Beginner / Intermediate / Expert", "Mines / Time", "Cleared! / Boom."

**Game features**
- Three classic difficulties: 9×9/10, 16×16/40, 16×30/99.
- First click is always safe (3×3 safe zone, mines placed after first reveal).
- Flood-fill reveal, number chord (tap revealed number with correct flag count to clear neighbors).
- Mine/time panel, reset button that shows `↻` / `↺` / `★` for new/lost/won.
- Flags via right-click (desktop), long-press (mobile), or a **Tap to: Reveal / Flag** toggle for mobile users who prefer single-tap flagging.
- Best times per difficulty persisted in `localStorage` under `minesweeper-best`.
- Responsive cell sizing, horizontal scroll for Expert on narrow screens, `touch-action: manipulation` + `gesturestart` prevention to stop pinch-zoom on the board.
- Subtle fade-in on load; hover lift on back button; no bounce/glow animations.
